Sometimed the world makes me feel small, like a tiny #fairy that could be squished or stepped on at any point. But how magical it is to be this small in the eyes of the world sometimes. I know some people, when they see me, all they see if the sum of my mistakes. They hate me, and may even want to squish me.. But an ego death can be a beautiful beginning! Ego is a dangerous thing to let get too big. We think ourselves invinsible, like we couldn’t possibly be in the wrong in anything we do. When we are faced with a force of correction, we fight back with heart & heat, but never our heads. The ego would never allow it. Being accountable shouldn’t be a difficult thing.. but Ego’s get in the way of growth & understanding. So check your ego on the regular. Dont let it define you, or control you. 💣 Bombshell of the Week 💣 
Hello, and happy Wednesday! 
Today we'd love to introduce you to the lovely Daddy Heda! 

You may have met her as Hobo Heda, Queen of Snacks but consider yourself informed! (Don't worry; we found out today, too. But we love new names!) 

The name may be a bit new, but Heda isn't! She's been attending Wasteland Weekend since 2019 and Neotropolis since 2023. 

Daddy Heda has been performing with the SoCal Nuclear Bombshells since 2019, but she's been a performer for most of her life. She was a cheerleader in high school and a theater kid. Hold your shock, please. 

She's also performed as a goblin for the Labyrinth of Jareth for years, singing and dancing with the crew and creating general mischief!
 
Daddy Heda is also a SAG Union Actor, a popular content creator with 1.6 million followers, and has made appearances at SDCC, Wondercon, and is an active LARPer! 

Daddy Heda has done it all, played princesses, clowns, goblins, and everything in between, but our favorite role is "Dance Mom" for the SoCal Bombshells because it's a tough job, and none of us want to do it. 

We love Daddy Heda and hope you do too!
